vectorData.altText: 13. Which of the following terms best describes the movement occurring at the hip joint in the accompanying video?
That's right! Flexion decrease the angle of the hip joint.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Flexion and Extension. Stand up and perform all the movements illustrated, starting from the anatomical position. Notice that flexion of the elbow brings the forearm forward, while flexion of the knee brings the leg backward.
Therefore, in general, the definition of flexion and extension have nothing to do with the direction of the movement, and everything to do with the change in angle between the articulating elements.
